= Create Class from Primitive =
#context: lop
#icon: Lop/create_class_from_primtive

"""Creates a USD class primitive and moves the hierarchy of a specified primitive into it."""

== Overview ==

Create Class from Primitive creates a new USD class prim and re-parents the hierarchy beneath the specified source primitive into it. Class prims in USD are used for inheriting opinions across many prims efficiently.

@parameters

Primitive:
    #id: primitive
    The source primitive whose hierarchy will be placed inside the new class prim.

Class:
    #id: class
    Name for the new class primitive. The specifier of the created prim will be `class`.

New Name:
    #id: new_name
    Optional new name for the top-level prim when it is moved into the class hierarchy.
